## Stock Footage System

### How It Works

The bot uses **local stock footage** as the video background. Videos are organized in category folders under [stock/](file:///d:/YouTubeBot/scripts/06_thumbnail.py#11-51).

### Adding New Categories

1. Create a new folder: `stock/your_category/`
2. Add [.mp4](file:///d:/YouTubeBot/stock/fire/11907039_3840_2160_30fps.mp4) files (any resolution, any frame rate)
3. Files must be > 100KB (smaller files are skipped)
4. The bot will automatically discover and use them

### Current Library

| Category | Clips | Size Range | Resolutions |
|----------|-------|------------|-------------|
| `fire/` | 8 | 5–48 MB | 1080p, 2K, 4K |
| `morning/` | 17 | 6–174 MB | 1080p, 1440p, 4K |
| `oceans/` | 7 | 5–66 MB | 1080p, 1440p, 4K |
| `plants/` | 12 | 5–126 MB | 1080p, 1440p, 4K |

> [!TIP]
> Get free stock footage from [Pexels](https://www.pexels.com/videos/), [Pixabay](https://pixabay.com/videos/), or [Coverr](https://coverr.co/). Any resolution works — the bot normalizes everything to 1920×1080.

### Normalization Process

Since stock clips come in wildly different formats, the bot **normalizes each clip** before concatenation:

```
Original clip (any format)
    ↓ FFmpeg re-encode
Normalized: 1920×1080, 30fps, h264, yuv420p, AAC audio
    ↓ FFmpeg concat demuxer
Final concatenated video
```

> [!NOTE]
> Clips without an audio track automatically get a silent audio stream injected so the concat demuxer doesn't crash.

---

## Known Issues & Fixes

### ✅ Fixed: Stock Videos Not Working (2026-03-21)

**Root Cause**: FFmpeg's `-f concat` demuxer requires **all input files** to have identical codec, resolution, frame rate, and pixel format. The stock clips ranged from 1080p to 4K and 24fps to 60fps — the concat demuxer either failed silently or produced corrupted/broken output.

**Fix Applied** in [05_make_video.py](file:///d:/YouTubeBot/scripts/05_make_video.py):
- Added a [normalize_clip()](file:///d:/YouTubeBot/scripts/05_make_video.py#52-109) function that re-encodes each clip to 1920×1080 @ 30fps with h264/yuv420p
- Clips without audio get a silent audio track injected (fallback encoding)
- Normalized clips are concatenated, then cleaned up to save disk space

**Fix Applied** in [04_get_footage.py](file:///d:/YouTubeBot/scripts/04_get_footage.py):
- [write_concat_file()](file:///d:/YouTubeBot/scripts/04_get_footage.py#115-127) now writes **absolute paths** instead of relative paths so FFmpeg resolves files correctly
- Fixed crash when only 1 stock category is available (line 148 `chosen[1]` → `' + '.join(chosen)`)

**Fix Applied** in [test_main.py](file:///d:/YouTubeBot/test_main.py):
- Added `output/clips_normalized` and `output/norm_concat.txt` to cleanup lists

### ⚠️ Known Limitation: [install.bat](file:///d:/YouTubeBot/install.bat) References Wrong Package

The install script installs `google-generativeai` (Gemini SDK) but the bot actually uses [groq](file:///d:/YouTubeBot/scripts/02_write_script.py#13-26). Should install:
```
pip install groq edge-tts pillow python-dotenv google-auth google-auth-oauthlib google-api-python-client
```

### ⚠️ Known Limitation: Thumbnail Upload Requires Channel Verification

YouTube requires channel verification to upload custom thumbnails via API. The bot handles this gracefully by skipping thumbnail upload with an informative message.

