## Running the Bot

### First Time Setup

```bash
# 1. Install Python dependencies
pip install groq edge-tts pillow python-dotenv google-auth google-auth-oauthlib google-api-python-client

# 2. Install FFmpeg (must be in PATH)
# Download from https://ffmpeg.org/download.html

# 3. Set up .env file with your API keys

# 4. Place YouTube OAuth credentials in credentials.json

# 5. Add stock footage to stock/ subfolders

# 6. Add background music as music/background.mp3
```

### Test Mode (Recommended First)

```bash
python test_main.py
```

- Creates 2 test videos
- **No upload** — saves to [temp/](file:///d:/YouTubeBot/test_main.py#39-72) folder
- Review the MP4 files before going live

### Production Mode

```bash
python main.py
```

- Creates 2 videos
- Uploads to YouTube
- Schedules at optimal IST times
- Archives videos to `archive/`
- Cleans [output/](file:///d:/YouTubeBot/scripts/02_write_script.py#90-122) folder between videos

### Run Individual Steps

```bash
python scripts/02_write_script.py    # Generate script only
python scripts/03_voiceover.py       # Generate voiceover only
python scripts/04_get_footage.py     # Select footage only
python scripts/05_make_video.py      # Assemble video only
python scripts/06_thumbnail.py       # Generate thumbnail only
python scripts/07_upload.py          # Upload only
```

